<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Parley1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Parley,</orth> subst. a conversation or conference tending to come to an agreement: <emph>in such a p.</emph> (of looks) <cit><quote>should I answer thee,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.204" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 1, 204</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>calls to p. the sleepers of the house,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 2.3.87" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 3, 87</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>what an eye she has! methinks it sounds a p. of provocation,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.23" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 23</bibl></cit> (Ff <emph>a p. to provocation</emph>). Chiefly a conference with enemies: <bibl n="shak. luc 471" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 471</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.1.68" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 1, 68</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.33" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 3, 33</bibl> (Qq <emph>parlee,</emph> Ff <emph>parle</emph>). <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.1.159" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 1, 159</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.2.149" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 2, 149</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.3.35" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 3, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.3.35" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 3, 35</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.3.35" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 3, 35</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.130" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 130</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.8.5" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 8, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.110" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 2, 110</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.4.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 4, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.1.159" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 159</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 5.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. V, 1, 21</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>